<sec sec-type="scope" id="id-203efb0f-c4db-4fd3-a17a-c36d13dab498"><title>Scope</title><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="8763689" change-id="2f5d780f-374d-4ef5-d179-ba072a93a736" text="The Scope clause is a mandatory element of the text.For rules on the drafting of the Scope, refer to the ISO/IEC Directives, Part 2:2018, Clause 14." timestamp="1656530016835"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="9276395" change-id="844c5a34-a58c-45f8-c8d8-3a9f4e1469a2" text="Concepts, terms and definitions;Identification of existing good practices;Definition of actions, strategies, policies for the promotion and implementation of gender equalityThe objective is to develop guidelines on:Standardization in the field of gender equality with the aim of developing a technical guidance on how to promote and implement gender equality in all types of organizations, public or private, regardless of their size, location and field of activity." timestamp="1668683323577"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="b2ab3a8b-a418-4265-dc4f-c91791cf210e" timestamp="1656530021141"?><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="b2ab3a8b-a418-4265-dc4f-c91791cf210e"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="9276395" change-id="45b7ffe2-f619-4669-851c-959ce31a483f" timestamp="1668683307689"?>This document gives guidance on how to promote and implement gender equality and women’s empowerment. It offers guidelines for organizations to develop the capabilities to achieve a culture of gender equality and women’s empowerment. The guidelines include the framework, resources, policies, tools and good practices enabling contextualization, promotion and implementation of gender equality. <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="45b7ffe2-f619-4669-851c-959ce31a483f"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="167da4b9-1c0b-44a7-f5b4-e4e5ae304333" timestamp="1656530021141"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="167da4b9-1c0b-44a7-f5b4-e4e5ae304333"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="9276395" change-id="722cc87e-e76a-4a1b-e1f6-36fbcc64dd4a" timestamp="1668683307689"?>This document focuses on the inequality resulting from the gender specific roles assigned to women, girls, men and boys and is applicable to all types of organisations - public or private, regardless of their size, location and field of activity.<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="722cc87e-e76a-4a1b-e1f6-36fbcc64dd4a"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="f6080ba3-d72f-4bc2-c0f3-8ba0067b25e6" timestamp="1656530021141"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="f6080ba3-d72f-4bc2-c0f3-8ba0067b25e6"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="9276395" change-id="f936ab1e-ca10-4b05-8d82-2cc15fcd0e11" timestamp="1668683307689"?>This document does not address the specific aspects of relations with labour unions or work councils, countries specific compliance and legal requirements on gender diversity.<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="f936ab1e-ca10-4b05-8d82-2cc15fcd0e11"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="76c76254-f2a7-4e4e-a968-8cde5c9f538c" timestamp="1656530021141"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="76c76254-f2a7-4e4e-a968-8cde5c9f538c"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="9276395" change-id="dd9f3016-e1a4-4f28-92c7-f3cba7940df1" timestamp="1668683307689"?>Note: Please refer to <italic>3.5 (now)</italic> definition of gender and <italic>3.21 (now)</italic> definition of diversity.<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="dd9f3016-e1a4-4f28-92c7-f3cba7940df1"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="22063b0b-3dd7-470d-f062-35203b2e2dc7" timestamp="1656530021141"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="22063b0b-3dd7-470d-f062-35203b2e2dc7"?></p></sec>